# Docker build context excludes for the itsm-platform monorepo.
# Keeps the build context small and, critically, keeps the GPL-3.0 GLPI
# reference clone (/source) OUT of any image we build.

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image via pnpm)
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Build outputs (regenerated inside the image)
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Version control / CI / editor
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Env files - never bake secrets into an image; pass them at runtime instead
# (.env.example is just a template and isn't needed to build or run the app).
# MUST be **/-prefixed: a bare ".env"/".env.*" pattern only matches at the
# build-context root in .dockerignore syntax (unlike .gitignore, it is NOT
# recursive by default) - a bare pattern here silently let apps/web/.env and
# apps/worker/.env get copied straight into shipped image layers.
**/.env
**/.env.*

# OS cruft
.DS_Store

# Reference-only material that must never end up in a shippable image
#  - /source is a clone of upstream GLPI (GPL-3.0), kept only for local
#    architecture/reference research, not part of our product.
#  - docs/graphify-out is generated knowledge-graph tooling output.
/source
docs/graphify-out

# Large reference docs not needed to build or run the app
*.pdf

# Misc project docs (not needed inside the image)
docs/**/*.md
README.md
